{"repo": "jldbc/pybaseball", "pull_number": 453, "instance_id": "jldbc__pybaseball-453", "issue_numbers": [451, 452], "base_commit": "691dbe33d314f38b874ccaf28ba4d265e6c3b361", "patch": "diff --git a/pybaseball/league_batting_stats.py b/pybaseball/league_batting_stats.py\nindex b13fda43..564dc1b1 100644\n--- a/pybaseball/league_batting_stats.py\n+++ b/pybaseball/league_batting_stats.py\n@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@ def get_soup(start_dt: date, end_dt: date) -> BeautifulSoup:\n     # if((start_dt is None) or (end_dt is None)):\n     #    print('Error: a date range needs to be specified')\n     #    return None\n-    url = \"http://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/daily.cgi?user_team=&bust_cache=&type=b&lastndays=7&dates=fromandto&fromandto={}.{}&level=mlb&franch=&stat=&stat_value=0\".format(start_dt, end_dt)\n+    url = \"https://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/daily.cgi?user_team=&bust_cache=&type=b&lastndays=7&dates=fromandto&fromandto={}.{}&level=mlb&franch=&stat=&stat_value=0\".format(start_dt, end_dt)\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     # a workaround to avoid beautiful soup applying the wrong encoding\n     s = s.decode('utf-8')\n@@ -92,7 +92,7 @@ def bwar_bat(return_all: bool = False) -> pd.DataFrame:\n     Get data from war_daily_bat table. Returns WAR, its components, and a few other useful stats.\n     To get all fields from this table, supply argument return_all=True.\n     \"\"\"\n-    url = \"http://www.baseball-reference.com/data/war_daily_bat.txt\"\n+    url = \"https://www.baseball-reference.com/data/war_daily_bat.txt\"\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     c=pd.read_csv(io.StringIO(s.decode('utf-8')))\n     if return_all:\n@@ -101,4 +101,4 @@ def bwar_bat(return_all: bool = False) -> pd.DataFrame:\n         cols_to_keep = ['name_common', 'mlb_ID', 'player_ID', 'year_ID', 'team_ID', 'stint_ID', 'lg_ID',\n                         'pitcher','G', 'PA', 'salary', 'runs_above_avg', 'runs_above_avg_off','runs_above_avg_def',\n                         'WAR_rep','WAA','WAR']\n-        return c[cols_to_keep]\n+        return c[cols_to_keep]\n\\ No newline at end of file\ndiff --git a/pybaseball/league_pitching_stats.py b/pybaseball/league_pitching_stats.py\nindex b140cb62..04c94533 100644\n--- a/pybaseball/league_pitching_stats.py\n+++ b/pybaseball/league_pitching_stats.py\n@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@ def get_soup(start_dt: Optional[Union[date, str]], end_dt: Optional[Union[date,\n     if((start_dt is None) or (end_dt is None)):\n         print('Error: a date range needs to be specified')\n         return None\n-    url = \"http://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/daily.cgi?user_team=&bust_cache=&type=p&lastndays=7&dates=fromandto&fromandto={}.{}&level=mlb&franch=&stat=&stat_value=0\".format(start_dt, end_dt)\n+    url = \"https://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/daily.cgi?user_team=&bust_cache=&type=p&lastndays=7&dates=fromandto&fromandto={}.{}&level=mlb&franch=&stat=&stat_value=0\".format(start_dt, end_dt)\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     # a workaround to avoid beautiful soup applying the wrong encoding\n     s = s.decode('utf-8')\n@@ -96,7 +96,7 @@ def bwar_pitch(return_all: bool=False) -> pd.DataFrame:\n     Get data from war_daily_pitch table. Returns WAR, its components, and a few other useful stats.\n     To get all fields from this table, supply argument return_all=True.\n     \"\"\"\n-    url = \"http://www.baseball-reference.com/data/war_daily_pitch.txt\"\n+    url = \"https://www.baseball-reference.com/data/war_daily_pitch.txt\"\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     c = pd.read_csv(io.StringIO(s.decode('utf-8')))\n     if return_all:\ndiff --git a/pybaseball/standings.py b/pybaseball/standings.py\nindex e6c13127..5e4296b2 100644\n--- a/pybaseball/standings.py\n+++ b/pybaseball/standings.py\n@@ -10,7 +10,7 @@\n session = BRefSession()\n \n def get_soup(year: int) -> BeautifulSoup:\n-    url = f'http://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/MLB/{year}-standings.shtml'\n+    url = f'https://www.baseball-reference.com/leagues/MLB/{year}-standings.shtml'\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     return BeautifulSoup(s, \"lxml\")\n \ndiff --git a/pybaseball/team_results.py b/pybaseball/team_results.py\nindex 09b7eea8..6e7c44ce 100644\n--- a/pybaseball/team_results.py\n+++ b/pybaseball/team_results.py\n@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@ def get_soup(season: Optional[int], team: str) -> BeautifulSoup:\n     # get most recent year's schedule if year not specified\n     if season is None:\n         season = most_recent_season()\n-    url = \"http://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/{}/{}-schedule-scores.shtml\".format(team, season)\n+    url = \"https://www.baseball-reference.com/teams/{}/{}-schedule-scores.shtml\".format(team, season)\n     print(url)\n     s = session.get(url).content\n     return BeautifulSoup(s, \"lxml\")\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "schedule_and_record no longer works \nschedule_and_record returns a ValueError, even when year and team abbreviation are valid. \r\n\r\n`ValueError: Data cannot be retrieved for this team/year combo. Please verify that your team abbreviation is accurate and that the team existed during the season you are searching for.`\nAll Baseball-Reference queries return 503 error\nThis issues has persisted since at least yesterday morning, but any attempts to use the requests module to access a B-R endpoint are returning an HTTP 503 \"Service Unavailable\" error message. This does not appear to be related to rate limiting, as that had previously returned the Sport Reference [bot policy page](https://www.sports-reference.com/bot-traffic.html) rather than a 503 error.\r\n\r\nThis issue presents itself when the Soup result of the request response is attempted to be parsed, usually throwing a \"list index out of range\" exception message.\n", "hints_text": "I believe this is part of a bigger issue related to Baseball-Reference queries which I've posted in #452 \n\nThis issue occurs because the BR interface is now an HTTPS url rather than HTTP. Updating these URLs is required.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I believe this is part of a bigger issue related to Baseball-Reference queries which I've posted in #452 \n\nThis issue occurs because the BR interface is now an HTTPS url rather than HTTP. Updating these URLs is required.\nLooks like it is still http in team_results.py. I am having the same issue\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/jldbc/pybaseball/commit/2e45e19409b71335d4f0069ab6dc3cc12472a2cd", "https://github.com/jldbc/pybaseball/commit/1a70af841708285f7157b8dda30666313fb142ca"], "created_at": "2024-09-08T20:39:39Z"}
